---
Name: Get All Projects
Description: Gets all projects in a Jira instance

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getAllProjects

---
Name: Get Project
Description: Gets a project in a Jira instance
Share Tools: Get All Projects
Args: projectIdOrKey: the ID or key of the project to get

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getProject

---
Name: Get All Users
Description: Gets all users in a Jira instance
Args: includeAppUsers: Optional, whether to include app users in the response. Defaults to false. 

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getAllUsers

---
Name: Get User
Description: Gets a user in a Jira instance
Share Tools: Get All Users
Args: accountId: the ID of the user to get

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getUser

---
Name: List Issues
Description: Lists all issues in a Jira project or all projects
Share Tools: Get Project, Get All Projects
Args: projectIdOrKey: Optional, the ID or key of the project to list the issues in

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js listIssues

---
Name: Get Issue
Description: Gets an issue in a Jira project
Share Tools: List Issues
Args: issueKey: the key of the issue to get

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getIssue

---
Name: Get Issue Types
Description: Gets the issue types in a Jira project. Each Jira project can have different issue types, so this is useful to get the issue types for a specific project, and can then be used to create an issue.
Share Tools: Get Project, Get All Projects
Args: projectIdOrKey: the ID or key of the project to get the issue types in

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getIssueTypes

---
Name: Get Priority Schemes
Description: Gets the priority schemes in a Jira instance.

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getPrioritySchemes

---
Name: Get Available Priorities
Description: Gets the available priorities of a priority scheme. if no schemeId is provided, it will get the default priority scheme.
Share Tools: Get Priority Schemes
Args: schemeId: Optional, the ID of the priority scheme to get the available priorities in.

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js getAvailablePriorities

---
Name: Create Issue
Description: Creates an issue in a Jira project
Share Tools: Get Issue Types, Get Available Priorities, Get User, Get Project
Args: projectId: the ID of the project to create the issue in
Args: summary: the summary/title of the issue
Args: description: Optional, the description of the issue.
Args: issueType: Optional, the type of the issue
Args: priority: Optional, the priority of the issue
Args: assigneeId: Optional, the account ID of the assignee of the issue
Args: reporterId: Optional, the account ID of the reporter of the issue

#!/usr/bin/env node --no-warnings ${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/index.js createIssue

